<dl id="s15035n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us15" href="#s15035n">Circe: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s15all.htm#s15035n">sector 35(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sounding Memnon</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The so called <mark>sounding Memnon</mark> is most sadly mutilated&mdash;the inscriptions upon it say, by Cambyses. A tradition&mdash;believed till not long since&mdash;has it, that it greeted the rising sun with a peculiar tone. Roman prefects, and emperors listened with devotion to the wondrous sound. In later times it was considered a freak of nature. <small> Moritz Busch. <a name="MBGE" href="/udra/udex.htm#MBGE"><cite title="source">Guide for Travellers to Egypt</cite></a> (1858), 102 [Thebes]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
